{"Name":"Autohide Navigation Bar","Id":1703,"Alias":"autohidenavigationbar","Description":"Auto hiding navigation bar like it can be seen in Facebook app, works out of the box with just few lines of code.\n\n```csharp\nusing IOSBITS.Controls;\n...\n\n// create new navigation controller with our type as the navigation bar\nnavigationController = new UINavigationController (typeof(AutohideNavigationBar), null);\n```\n","Version":"1.2","Summary":"Adds autohide navigation bar to your Xamarin iOS apps.","QuickStart":"First add reference to the lib and start using it.\n\n```csharp\nusing IOSBITS.Controls;\n```\n\nIn the application\u0027s AppDelegete (or anywhere else where you create the navigation controller) add the class **AuthohideNavigationBar** as the navigation bar class.\n\n```csharp\nusing IOSBITS.Controls;\n...\n\npublic override bool FinishedLaunching (UIApplication app, NSDictionary options)\n{\n\twindow = new UIWindow (UIScreen.MainScreen.Bounds);\n\t\t\t\n\t// this is our sample view controller that has table view in it\n\tviewController = new SampleViewController ();\n\t\t\t\n\t// create new navigation controller with our type as the navigation bar\n\tnavigationController = new UINavigationController (typeof(AutohideNavigationBar), null);\n\t\t\t\n\t// this next is just standard app initialization\n\tnavigationController.ViewControllers = new UIViewController[] { viewController };\n\twindow.RootViewController = navigationController;\n\twindow.MakeKeyAndVisible ();\n\t\t\t\n\treturn true;\n}\n```\n\nThen in the actual view controller that has the scrollview (tableview or similar), set it so it can handle the actual scrolling.\n\n```csharp\npublic override void ViewWillAppear (bool animated)\n{\n\tbase.ViewWillAppear (animated);\n\n\tNavigationItem.Title = @\"Sample Autohiding\";\n\n\t// assign the table view (or any other scrollview) as the scrollview to navigation bar, this will hook the gestures and make the whole magic work\n\tNavigationController.GetAutohideNavigationBar().ScrollView = this.TableView;\n}\n\npublic override void ViewWillDisappear (bool animated)\n{\n\tbase.ViewWillDisappear (animated);\n\n\t// don\u0027t forget to deregister on disapear\n\tNavigationController.GetAutohideNavigationBar().ScrollView = null;\n}\n```\n\nThat is all there is to it. Component just does all the handling for you. Check out the **sample**.","Hash":"ff57b8b0539d1702b01b4330c1a4dfc3","TargetPlatforms":["ios"],"TrialHash":null}